//dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Chen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Chen\"}, {\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nathan Chen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathan_Chen\"}, {\"begin\": 1497, \"end\": 1510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madison Chock\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Chock\"}, {\"begin\": 1512, \"end\": 1527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zachary_Donohue\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zachary Donohue\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zachary_Donohue\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zachary_Donohue\"}, {\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_Frazier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brandon Frazier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_Frazier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_Frazier\"}, {\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Hubbell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madison Hubbell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Hubbell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Hubbell\"}, {\"begin\": 1563, \"end\": 1576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexa_Knierim\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexa Knierim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexa_Knierim\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexa_Knierim\"}, {\"begin\": 1581, \"end\": 1593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Zhou\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vincent Zhou\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Zhou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Zhou\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At Tuesday's press conference the head of the U.S. Olympic and Paralympic Committee, Sarah Hirshland, described the outcome as a win for clean, drug-free sport.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1682, \"end\": 1687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\", \"score\": 0.6508513381698867, \"rank\": 0.2696400922433112, \"text\": \"Sarah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Geronimo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is about celebration,\\\" Hirshland said.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's also about having hope that a system is growing and improving, insuring that all athletes from around the world can count on showing up to compete on a level playing field.\\\"\", \"from\": 1804, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The honor - the first-ever team Olympic skating gold medal for the U.S. - was delayed because of adoping scandal involving Russian star skater Kamila Valieva.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9286012598201876, \"rank\": 0.07594413282632471, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 2128, \"end\": 2134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9999999945716809, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kamila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She was allowed to compete in Beijing despite a prior test that showed she had used a cardiac medication that's banned as a performance enhancing drug.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2296, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2175, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9996674666218719, \"rank\": 0.0003326439932930853, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her masterful skating helped elevate the Russian team to an apparent gold-medal victory, buta final ruling Monday by the Court of Arbitration for Sport(CAS) disqualified her performance.\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2339, \"end\": 2346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9286012598201876, \"rank\": 0.07594413282632471, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In its ruling Monday, CAS banned Valieva from the sport through the end of 2025 and disqualified all her performances dating back to December 2021.\", \"from\": 2486, \"to\": 2633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2508, \"end\": 2511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.768586008239049e-35, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking on Tuesday, Olympic skater Evan Bates - one of the new gold medal winners - said the wait was excruciating, but he described the outcome as a vindication.\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is a landmark case, this a monumental thing, an unprecedented event,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2800, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Clean athletes left the Olympics without a medal they won cleanly.\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The finding by CAS brought some justice to the clean sport movement.\\\"\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 3022, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2968, \"end\": 2971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.768586008239049e-35, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not clear when a formal award ceremony will be held to honor U.S. skaters, as well as Japanese athletes now in line to win silver.\", \"from\": 3024, \"to\": 3159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking on Tuesday, American athletes said they hope to be honored in Paris during the Summer Olympics that begin in July 2024.\", \"from\": 3160, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3181, \"end\": 3189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998669357044, \"rank\": 1.0721872594161373e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3231, \"end\": 3236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999373408193, \"rank\": 6.265936079877724e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Canadians, who placed fourth, did not move up to the bronze.In its final tabulations, the International Skating Union says even with the Valieva disqualification, Russia secured enough points to claim the bronze.\", \"from\": 3290, \"to\": 3506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3406, \"end\": 3411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999885521903, \"rank\": 1.1445201070679493e-08, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3457, \"end\": 3463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.9834811278638725, \"rank\": 0.016791822411559132, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement, Skate Canada said it is \\\"extremely disappointed\\\" with the tabulation and will \\\"consider all options to appeal this decision.\\\"\", \"from\": 3508, \"to\": 3649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3524, \"end\": 3536, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_Skate_Canada_International\", \"score\": 0.9826409992558772, \"rank\": 0.01766476992228604, \"text\": \"Skate Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_Skate_Canada_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2019_Skate_Canada_International\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. officials acknowledged that lingering controversy on Tuesday, but said it will not affect the gold medal status of American athletes.\", \"from\": 3651, \"to\": 3789, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3771, \"end\": 3779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998669357044, \"rank\": 1.0721872594161373e-07, \"text\": \"American\", 